Lawish boasts of being earthquake resistant. Architect Vilas Tarwadi and structural designer Hansal Parikh & Associates have collaborated to come up with this elegant and awe-inspiring project. Each flat is constructed and designed with top of the line products. Keeping in mind the importance of sustainable living, each flat is incorporated with solar-system water in washrooms. The occasional power-cuts become easier to handle with the generators provided with each building. Every flat in each of the three buildings of LaWish has terraces in the living room and the master bedroom and a standing terrace. These lend an airy atmosphere and sun-bathing opportunities but with the privacy of your own house.  These captivating 2BHK flats in Pisoli are updated with a high-end modern security system. All the flats have a video door phone with intercom. There is a fire fighting system in each building to help in case of an emergency. Lawish also provides to look after your overall health. It has a well-equipped gymnasium, a jogging track, an acupressure park and yoga and meditation room and also swimming pools for both, adults and toddlers. The senior citizens have a park all to themselves while the children have a soft play area specially designed for them. The amphitheatre, party lawn, and recreation hall allows you to host small get-together and parties for special occasions. The temple in the N/E of the project engulfs the property with the Almightys blessings. The internal concrete roads and the 2-level car parking area is a boon for the car owners.  What makes these flats in Pisoli even more favorable is its location. Pisoli, Pune is exceptionally well-connected. It is a mere 12 km away from Pune railway station while the Katraj bus station is 15 mins away. The Pune Airport is 19 KM from here. The Satara and Solapur highways are also easily reached. The quite famous Rajiv Gandhi Zoological Park is barely 4 KMs away from Pisoli while the ISKCON NVCC temple is 19 mins away. Pisolis proximity to the schools (Bishops School, Hill Green School), colleges and universities (Sinhagad Institute, Bharti Vidyapeeth), E Square Multiplex, Nobel Hospital and petrol pumps is attractive.

Lawish boasts of being earthquake resistant. Architect Vilas Tarwadi and structural designer Hansal Parikh & Associates have collaborated to come up with this elegant and awe-inspiring project. Each flat is constructed and designed with top of the line products. Keeping in mind the importance of sustainable living, each flat is incorporated with solar-system water in washrooms. The occasional power-cuts become easier to handle with the generators provided with each building. Every flat in each of the three buildings of LaWish has terraces in the living room and the master bedroom and a standing terrace. These lend an airy atmosphere and sun-bathing opportunities but with the privacy of your own house.  These captivating 2BHK flats in Pisoli are updated with a high-end modern security system. All the flats have a video door phone with intercom. There is a fire fighting system in each building to help in case of an emergency. Lawish also provides to look after your overall health. It has a well-equipped gymnasium, a jogging track, an acupressure park and yoga and meditation room and also swimming pools for both, adults and toddlers. The senior citizens have a park all to themselves while the children have a soft play area specially designed for them. The amphitheatre, party lawn, and recreation hall allows you to host small get-together and parties for special occasions. The temple in the N/E of the project engulfs the property with the Almightys blessings. The internal concrete roads and the 2-level car parking area is a boon for the car owners.  What makes these flats in Pisoli even more favorable is its location. Pisoli, Pune is exceptionally well-connected. It is a mere 12 km away from Pune railway station while the Katraj bus station is 15 mins away. The Pune Airport is 19 KM from here. The Satara and Solapur highways are also easily reached. The quite famous Rajiv Gandhi Zoological Park is barely 4 KMs away from Pisoli while the ISKCON NVCC temple is 19 mins away. Pisolis proximity to the schools (Bishops School, Hill Green School), colleges and universities (Sinhagad Institute, Bharti Vidyapeeth), E Square Multiplex, Nobel Hospital and petrol pumps is attractive.

Nisargayan is an eco-friendly resort nestled amidst the Sahyadri Ranges  (1100 ft above the sea level)  precisely at Palu village in Murbad taluka near Kalyan.   The birds chirp in the background, the forest glade radiates a mellow tranquillity...the citys hustle & bustle seems far away. Early morning youll wake up to a sunrise you will never forget. The sunrays illuminate the trees in the lush green. If you are an adventure lover, you can always go for a half day trek or drive to Nane Ghat or Malshej Ghat that landscapes the property. The river outside the resort will leave you stunned - sit around it listening to the sound of the water...aaah.. such bliss!!! Besides, you can always visit this lake behind the resort to experience another level of serenity. Walk a few minutes more, and even another rendezvous with nature awaits you  a mesmerizing Waterfall!!  All the cottages are well-maintained and furnished, and have huge verandahs. The nights are serene too. You would not want to go for any star-gazing trip with those adventure groups because you will experience this too at night. Lie down in your verandah or the lawn outside your cottage and enjoy the star-lit sky, in the company of fireflies...

Lawish boasts of being earthquake resistant. Architect Vilas Tarwadi and structural designer Hansal Parikh & Associates have collaborated to come up with this elegant and awe-inspiring project. Each flat is constructed and designed with top of the line products. Keeping in mind the importance of sustainable living, each flat is incorporated with solar-system water in washrooms. The occasional power-cuts become easier to handle with the generators provided with each building. Every flat in each of the three buildings of LaWish has terraces in the living room and the master bedroom and a standing terrace. These lend an airy atmosphere and sun-bathing opportunities but with the privacy of your own house.  These captivating 2BHK flats in Pisoli are updated with a high-end modern security system. All the flats have a video door phone with intercom. There is a fire fighting system in each building to help in case of an emergency. Lawish also provides to look after your overall health. It has a well-equipped gymnasium, a jogging track, an acupressure park and yoga and meditation room and also swimming pools for both, adults and toddlers. The senior citizens have a park all to themselves while the children have a soft play area specially designed for them. The amphitheatre, party lawn, and recreation hall allows you to host small get-together and parties for special occasions. The temple in the N/E of the project engulfs the property with the Almightys blessings. The internal concrete roads and the 2-level car parking area is a boon for the car owners.  What makes these flats in Pisoli even more favorable is its location. Pisoli, Pune is exceptionally well-connected. It is a mere 12 km away from Pune railway station while the Katraj bus station is 15 mins away. The Pune Airport is 19 KM from here. The Satara and Solapur highways are also easily reached. The quite famous Rajiv Gandhi Zoological Park is barely 4 KMs away from Pisoli while the ISKCON NVCC temple is 19 mins away. Pisolis proximity to the schools (Bishops School, Hill Green School), colleges and universities (Sinhagad Institute, Bharti Vidyapeeth), E Square Multiplex, Nobel Hospital and petrol pumps is attractive.
